==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stethoscope
<hw>Steth"o*scope</hw> <pr>(st⟦ecr⟧th"⟦osl⟧*sk⟦omac⟧p)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>sth^qos</grk> the breast +
<ets>-scope</ets>: cf. F. <ets>st⟦eacute⟧thoscope</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>An instrument used in auscultation for examining
the organs of the chest, as the heart and lungs, by conveying to the ear
of the examiner the sounds produced in the thorax.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stethoscope</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stethoscope
<hw>Steth"o*scope</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To auscultate, or examine,
with a stethoscope.</def> <rj><au>M. W. Savage.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stethoscopical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Stethoscopic</ent>⟦br⟧
